This patch add a small condition when setting the Digester publicId value. When a parser try to resolve a DTD, the first validation will contains the proper dtd public's ID, but second invokation will be equal to null. This patch fixes a bug in Tomcat 4.0 and 5.0. Submitted by:	Jean-Francois Arcand (jeanfrancois.arcand@sun.com)

Allow multiple CallMethodRule rules to be fired on the same pattern.  The problem was that each CallMethodRule was pushing its parameter array onto the object stack, which interfered with the ultimate method call on the top" data object.  This was fixed by using a separate stack for the the parameter arrays."
